---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import Button from "../components/ui/Button.astro";
import Card from "../components/ui/Card.astro";
import Kicker from "../components/ui/Kicker.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
    title="Privacy Policy — Never Sleep"
    description="How Never Sleep handles permissions, local settings, and Google AdMob advertising."
>
    <article class="doc">
        <Kicker>Legal</Kicker>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lede">Last updated: July 9, 2026</p>
        <div class="actions doc-actions">
            <Button href="/">Back to home</Button>
            <Button
                href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.lizz.neversleep"
                variant="secondary"
                external={true}
            >
                Google Play
            </Button>
        </div>

        <Card>
            <section>
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                    Never Sleep is an Android utility that changes your device screen-off timeout when you
                    explicitly enable the feature. We designed the app to work with minimal data collection.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Information we process</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Screen timeout setting</strong> — When you turn Never Sleep on, the app
                        writes a higher value to Android’s system screen-off timeout and stores your
                        previous timeout locally so it can be restored.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>App preferences</strong> — Stored on your device only (e.g. whether ads are
                        disabled, whether Never Sleep was last enabled).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Advertising data</strong> — If ads are enabled, Google AdMob may collect
                        device identifiers and usage signals to serve and measure ads. See
                        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Google’s Privacy Policy</a>.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>What we do not do</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>We do not operate user accounts or collect names, emails, or contacts.</li>
                    <li>We do not sell your personal information.</li>
                    <li>
                        We do not upload your screen-timeout preference to our servers — it stays on your
                        device.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Permissions</h2>
                <p>
                    <strong>Modify system settings</strong> — Required for the core feature. You grant this
                    manually in Android Settings → Apps → Special app access.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Internet &amp; network state</strong> — Used only when banner ads are enabled, so
                    AdMob can load ads. You can disable ads in the in-app Settings menu.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Children</h2>
                <p>
                    Never Sleep is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal
                    information from children.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Changes</h2>
                <p>
                    We may update this policy. The “Last updated” date at the top will change when we do.
                    Continued use of the app after changes means you accept the revised policy.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Contact</h2>
                <p>
                    Questions about this policy? Open an issue in the project repository or contact the
                    developer through your Play Store listing support channel.
                </p>
            </section>
        </Card>
    </article>
</SiteLayout>